    "title": "Industrial Floor Coatings for Commercial Kitchens - Elite South Texas",
    "content": "Commercial Kitchens\nMaintaining a clean commercial kitchen, while adhering to local, state and federal regulations, can be extremely difficult. Protective resinous coatings offer several advantages over traditional flooring such as conventionally used commercial tile. Our surfaces are slip resistance, stain resistant, antimicrobial and are easy to clean and maintain. Optional thermal shock resistant flooring available for forced steam cleaning or boiling water.\nAdvantages\nAnti-microbial with no grout lines\nSeamless and non-porous\nThermal shock resistant\nVariable slip resistance and coefficient of friction\nResistant to chemicals and food spillage\nAbrasion resistant\nEasy to clean and maintain\nFDA, USDA* and CFIA** acceptable\nVertical applications for wall protection\nSuitable for extreme heat or cold conditions\nVariety of standard colors with custom colors on request\n* Can be used in USDA facilities based on FSIS Directive 11,000.4 (Rev. 1), November 24, 1995.\n** Agriculture Canada (also known as Canadian Food Inspection Agency).\nCommercial kitchens, delis and butcheries\nRestaurants\nSchool cafeterias\nFreezers and cold storage\nWarehouses and food storage\nPackaging and food processing\nParamount\nUrethane Cement",
